Generation logic
1) Content plan by sentiment
- 5 stars: Lead with highlight, mention 2–3 specifics (service speed, friendliness, quality), close with recommendation and return intent.
- 4 stars: Praise with one mild nitpick or suggestion.
- 3 stars: Balanced: 1–2 positives, 1–2 negatives, neutral tone.
- 2 stars: Polite, constructive: 1 concrete issue, suggest improvement, acknowledge any redeeming point.
- 1 star: Factual description of issues, avoid speculation, invite resolution.

2) Tone shaping
- Casual: contractions, simple sentences, light emojis if allowed.
- Professional: complete sentences, no slang, objective phrasing.
- Enthusiastic: energetic verbs, exclamation judiciously, vivid descriptors.
- Concise: tight phrasing, no redundancy.

3) Platform compliance
- Truncate to charLimit while preserving coherence.
- Remove disallowed formats or phrases.
- Optional headline if required.

4) Variability
- Synonym pools for openings, transitions, closings.
- Shuffle order of details.
